								<td class="stock-ticker"><div class="content">
										<p align="center"><strong>Late payment fees<br />
									    </strong>The High Court has delivered judgment in <a href="http://eresources.hcourt.gov.au/showCase/2016/HCA/28" target="_blank">Paciocco v Australia and New Zealand Banking Group Limited [2016] HCA 28 (27 July 2016)</a>. The case involved consideration of (amongst other things) late payment fees; in particular, whether they breach statutory prohibitions relating to unconscionable conduct and/or unfair terms and whether or not they constitute a 'penalty'.</p>
										<p align="center">The High Court dismissed both appeals, finding that the fees were not penalties and nor did they contravene statutory provisions</p>
										<p align="center">See also <a href="http://www.hcourt.gov.au/cases/case_m219-2015" target="_blank"><br />
									    High Court case resources page</a>.</p>
